## Map and terrain

Peel Park belies it's name. Classic 'parkland' is about 5% of the total area. The other 95% is either rough open moorland with scattered trees or classic orienteering woodland, plus many classic orienteering features. Take care near steep sided ravines!

The Peel Park map has been updated for this event to incorporate:

-  recent fire damage - this has made some moorland areas more runnable - mountain bike tracks - these are new and numerous on the steeper slopes, but only the most used are shown as paths on the map. Take special care if using these tracks.- forestry work - mostly thining work which may have improved runnability, but leaving scattered logs.- dog walkers tracks - there are many incidental tracks, especially on the open moorland, which are not marked on the map.

